            <h6>The contiuum</h6>
            <p>According to The Oxford Wiki (Millett, 2012) , the dissemination of Roman language, traditions, and culture across the empire was known as "Romanization." Romanization had slowly been implemented throughout the succeeding years of the Roman Empire which led to a a feeling of common identity across many groups leading to cultural assimilation. This caused lessened prejudice based on different societal levels, e.g. ethnical regions </p>
        </section>
